      "*": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:302px;\"><a href=\"/File:John_Cage_(1988).jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/23/John_Cage_%281988%29.jpg/330px-John_Cage_%281988%29.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"400\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/23/John_Cage_%281988%29.jpg/500px-John_Cage_%281988%29.jpg 1.5x, https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/23/John_Cage_%281988%29.jpg/960px-John_Cage_%281988%29.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/File:John_Cage_(1988).jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>John Cage (1988)</div></div></div>\n<p><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/John_Cage\">John Cage</a>, (September 5, 1912 – August 12, 1992)<br />\nwas an American artist, composer and music theorist.\n</p>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_Links\">External Links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Category:John_Cage&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: External Links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://johncage.org/\">John Cage&#160;:: Official Website</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Category:John_Cage\">Category:John Cage - Wikimedia Commons</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.openculture.com/2017/09/when-john-cage-marcel-duchamp-played-chess-on-a-chessboard-that-turned-chess-moves-into-electronic-music-1968.html\">When John Cage &amp; Marcel Duchamp Played Chess on a Chessboard That Turned Chess Moves Into Electronic Music (1968) | Open Culture</a>, September 27, 2017 